data.description: A Magnificent 1924 Craftsman Bungalow with modern upgrades. Move in ready with fresh paint, refinished floors, and a new shower. The original charm remains including hardwood flooring, original glass windows, exposed roof tail rafters on the original wood exterior, and an inviting front porch. Large sunlit living room that opens to the formal dining room. Party deck in the back, 8 ft. privacy fence, storage building, and a 187 ft. deep lot. Upgraded kitchen and laundry room with modern appliances, granite counters & a farmhouse sink. All appliances included. Modernized plumbing, HVAC, tankless electric water heater, and energy efficient insulation. Well maintained foundation. Located in Junius Heights Historic District, which is minutes from Downtown, Lakewood, and White Rock Lake. An active neighborhood association - part of 4 contiguous Historical Districts in Old East Dallas -with a home tour, spring fling, and block parties.
